From: Selvan Mani <smani@micron.com>
Date: Wed, 7 Nov 2012 06:03:56 -0700
Subject: mtip32xx: Fix incorrect mask used for erase mode
Git-commit: 4b9e884523f63f7bfd6fcbcdfe6f9f9545d98c13
References: FATE#311167
Patch-Mainline: v3.7

Previous commit use value 3 for erasemode mask.
Changing the mask to correct value to 2

Signed-off-by: Selvan Mani <smani@micron.com>
Signed-off-by: Asai Thambi S P <asamymuthupa@micron.com>
Signed-off-by: Jens Axboe <axboe@kernel.dk>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/block/mtip32xx/mtip32xx.h |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/block/mtip32xx/mtip32xx.h b/drivers/block/mtip32xx/mtip32xx.h
index 95a6bb1..432e53f 100644
--- a/drivers/block/mtip32xx/mtip32xx.h
+++ b/drivers/block/mtip32xx/mtip32xx.h
@@ -35,7 +35,7 @@
 #define PCIE_CONFIG_EXT_DEVICE_CONTROL_OFFSET	0x48
 
 /* check for erase mode support during secure erase */
-#define MTIP_SEC_ERASE_MODE     0x3
+#define MTIP_SEC_ERASE_MODE     0x2
 
 /* # of times to retry timed out/failed IOs */
 #define MTIP_MAX_RETRIES	2
